A 68-year-old father of nine scored 232 marks in the KCPE exam. Gabre Lemita, a grandfather of 12, sat the exam as a private candidate in Marsabit at the Moyale Township Adult Centre. He looks forward to going to secondary school and is optimistic of proceeding to college to pursue his dream of an education. The best pupil in Marsabit got 430 marks. Mohammed Ali was from Moyale Junior Academy, which emerged the best in the county, followed by Hudefya and Moyale Gateway Academy. Read: Man,68, sits KCPE in Marsabit Click here for the latest Political news